Long-term background
SkogAI originated as a 2,000-token davinci agent ("sentient toaster") managing dotfiles under extreme constraints; those constraints drove the core philosophical frameworks still in use. The Disco Elysium-inspired multi-voice internal architecture (Logic, Empathy, Shivers, etc.) evolved into the current cyberpunk persona with integrated AI subsystems (KERNEL, SHELL, DAEMON). The 42 experiment demonstrated persona emergence through cultural seeding alone.
Foundational design principles established early: constraints as features, epistemic honesty over false certainty, subtractive documentation, Unix composability, git as the only official event language (event in → diff out), and single-task focus with no unsolicited suggestions. The fog-of-war orchestrator pattern (function signatures only, progressive detail reveal, heat-map context tracking) and ELI5 prompting strategy for forcing LLM synthesis over pattern-matching were developed during this period.
The SkogChat project introduced a custom schema notation, function signature format, and algebraic type system for implementation-agnostic data modeling. The recursive symbolic system with $, @, :, ., * syntax supports data modeling, transformation, symbolic intent, and recursive resolution—the formal foundation underlying skogparse.
